      "level": { "value": 5 },
      "blurb": "Korvosan Noble, House Aldicott Dock Master",
      "publicNotes": "<p>An aging Korvosan noble, thinned by paranoia and minor alchemy. He carries himself with the brittle dignity of a man who has survived longer than he expected to. He controls House Aldicott's dock revenue through a network of informants and minor alchemists, and speaks slowly, choosing each word as if it might be poisoned.</p>",
      "privateNotes": "<p>Believes the PCs are assassins sent by a rival noble house. Will negotiate if approached with proof of a common enemy. Does not fight unless cornered — prefers negotiation, bribery, or summoning the Korvosan Guard. If combat begins, uses Silver Tongue reaction defensively, falls back to the inner room, and triggers Bodyguard Summons on round 2.</p>",
